cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Name: Request for Tender for the provision of Primary Care Services to the Irish Defence Forces
cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Description: What the Primary Care Clinic will involve a walk-in Primary Care service, provided each morning and in the afternoon as required, in military barracks. This involves: • Patient assessment and treatment/follow up, as necessary • Awarding of the appropriate occupational disposal (this is explained below) • Processing all follow up referrals/requests for reports, laboratory and radiological investigations • Management of secondary and tertiary referrals via Healthlink, with Defence Force sanction form for same completed at time of consultation • Maintenance of electronic health record • Ongoing review of medical condition
